# plan/facts/14-panel-of-experts-mutawatir.bn
#
# Mutawatir-equivalent L3 research synthesis for the cross-witness /
# panel-of-experts / multi-agent pattern. Composes existing facts/06
# bleeding-edge citations with 3 new (M3.40) recent independent groups
# specifically demonstrating MULTI-AGENT (not just multi-sample) lift
# over single-LLM dispatch.
#
# Per mizaj rule 16 (research-as-experiment-equivalent): N>=3 independent
# peer-reviewed groups converging on same conclusion = mutawatir-
# equivalent at L3 ceiling 0.85. Per mizaj rule 11, L3 cap holds unless
# L1 own-measurement composes alongside.
#
# 'illah for transfer to cheapcode-witness v1x (per mizaj rule 5):
#   - Same model class: LLMs
#   - Same pattern shape: multi-witness sampling + aggregation
#   - Same target tasks: hard reasoning / math / code
#   - cheapcode-witness v1x architecture is SPECIFICALLY layered MoA-style
#     (cheap × 2 + frontier-d in parallel → synthesizer aggregating layer)
#   - Different specific models but same architectural primitive

# ============================================================
# NEW citations added M3.40 (panel-of-experts specifically)
# ============================================================

# Mixture-of-Agents (Wang et al. 2024, arxiv 2406.04692, ICLR-rated)
# Layered MoA architecture: each layer = multiple LLM agents using
# outputs from prior layer as context. AlpacaEval 2.0: 65.1% MoA vs
# 57.5% GPT-4o = +7.6pp improvement using only open-source models.
# DIRECT match for cheapcode-witness v1x architecture.
lemma mixture_of_agents_layered_panel_beats_gpt4o_7_6pp_alpacaeval_l3
  proves True
  by audit arxiv-2406-04692-ICLR-2024-fetched-2026-05-03

# Multiagent Debate (Du, Li, Torralba, Tenenbaum, Mordatch 2023,
# arxiv 2305.14325, MIT/CSAIL). Multiple LLM instances debate across
# rounds → significantly enhances mathematical + strategic reasoning,
# reduces hallucinations + factual errors. Pattern: independent
# proposers + multi-round adjudication.
lemma multiagent_debate_lifts_math_strategic_reasoning_reduces_hallucinations_l3_2023
  proves True
  by audit arxiv-2305-14325-mit-csail-fetched-2026-05-03

# Agent Forest / "More Agents Is All You Need" (Li et al. 2024,
# arxiv 2402.05120, TMLR October 2024). Sampling-and-voting scales LLM
# performance with number of agent instances. Effectiveness correlates
# with TASK DIFFICULTY — direct support for "panel works on HARD
# reasoning" claim. Pattern: parallel sampling + voting aggregation
# (matches voter v0; also relevant for v1x panel).
lemma agent_forest_sampling_voting_scales_with_agents_correlates_with_difficulty_l3_tmlr_2024
  proves True
  by audit arxiv-2402-05120-tmlr-2024-fetched-2026-05-03

# ============================================================
# Composition with existing facts/06 + facts/03 citations
# ============================================================
#
# Existing L3 group at L3 (per facts/06):
#   1. Optimal Self-Consistency (arxiv 2511.12309, Nov 2025) — power-law
#      scaling with sample count
#   2. Adaptive Test-Time Compute (arxiv 2604.14853) — Level-3 hard
#      questions: +7.2-8.5pp from 1→16 samples
#   3. Forest-of-Thought (arxiv 2412.09078, Dec 2024) — test-time
#      compute scaling
#   4. Self-Consistency (Wang et al., 2022) — +18% on math reasoning
#   5. Difficulty-Adaptive Self-Consistency (NAACL 2025)
#   6. Survey of Test-Time Compute (2025)
# (facts/06 covers these.)
#
# NEW M3.40 additions (this file):
#   7. Mixture-of-Agents (Wang et al. 2024)
#   8. Multiagent Debate (Du et al. 2023)
#   9. Agent Forest (Li et al. 2024)
#
# Plus production-deployment evidence (facts/05):
#   - Anthropic Claude Code orchestrator + sub-agents
#   - Cognition Devin (compound architecture)
#   - NVIDIA NeMo Agent Toolkit
#
# TOTAL: 9+ academic groups + 3+ production deployments
# = MUTAWATIR-EQUIVALENT at L3 ceiling per mizaj 11 + 14.

lemma panel_of_experts_pattern_mutawatir_at_L3_via_9_plus_independent_groups_2026_05_03
  proves True
  by audit cheapcode-facts-14-research-synthesis-m3-40

